      "question": "A local NGO is organizing a charity event to distribute food packets. They have two types of delivery routes: Route A, represented by the linear equation $2x + y = 10$, and Route B, represented by the linear equation $x - y = 2$, where $x$ represents the distance covered in km and $y$ represents the fuel consumption in litres. The NGO volunteers need to analyze these routes to optimize their distribution.\n\n(i) If we plot the lines $2x + y = 10$ and $x - y = 2$ on a Cartesian plane, what are the coordinates of the point of intersection of these two lines?\n(ii) At what point does the line $2x + y = 10$ intersect the $x$-axis?\n(iii) What is the nature of the lines represented by the pair of equations $x - y = 2$ and $2x - 2y = 4$?\n(iv) If a new route is introduced as $x + y = k$ and it is known to pass through the point of intersection found in part (i), find the value of $k$.",
      "type": "case_study",
      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "The point of intersection of $2x + y = 10$ and $x - y = 2$ is:",
          "answer": "(A)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $(4, 2)$",
            "(B) $(2, 4)$",
            "(C) $(3, 1)$",
            "(D) $(5, 0)$"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Add the two equations: $(2x + y) + (x - y) = 10 + 2$.",
              "$3x = 12 \\Rightarrow x = 4$.",
              "Substitute $x = 4$ into $x - y = 2$: $4 - y = 2 \\Rightarrow y = 2$.",
              "The point is $(4, 2)$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$2x + y = 10 \\\\ x - y = 2 \\\\ (2x + y) + (x - y) = 10 + 2 \\\\ 3x = 12 \\\\ x = 4 \\\\ 4 - y = 2 \\\\ y = 2 \\\\ \\text{Point} = (4, 2)$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the $x$-intercept of the line $2x + y = 10$.",
          "answer": "$(5, 0)$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "The $x$-axis intercept occurs where $y = 0$.",
              "Substitute $y = 0$ in $2x + y = 10$.",
              "$2x + 0 = 10 \\Rightarrow 2x = 10 \\Rightarrow x = 5$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$2x + y = 10 \\\\ \\text{Set } y = 0 \\\\ 2x + 0 = 10 \\\\ x = 5 \\\\ \\text{Point} = (5, 0)$"
          }
