            "(B) Parallel",
            "(C) Coincident",
            "(D) Perpendicular"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Compare the ratios: $a_1/a_2 = 1/2$, $b_1/b_2 = -1/-2 = 1/2$, $c_1/c_2 = -2/-4 = 1/2$.",
              "Since $1/2 = 1/2 = 1/2$, the lines are coincident."
            ],
            "derivation": "$a_1/a_2 = 1/2 \\\\ b_1/b_2 = -1/-2 = 1/2 \\\\ c_1/c_2 = -2/-4 = 1/2 \\\\ \\frac{a_1}{a_2} = \\frac{b_1}{b_2} = \\frac{c_1}{c_2} \\\\ \\Rightarrow \\text{Coincident lines}$"
          }
